Ahead of the Champions League final against Real Madrid, Liverpool forward Mohamed Salah refused to discuss any transfer speculation but admits he will be staying next season. The Egyptian star said he is very motivated to the roof ahead of their Champions League duel with Real Madrid next weekend. But when asked about his contract with the Reds, Salah said he doesn't want to be selfish by talking about it but admitted that he will stay at the club next season. "I'm just focused with the team...we have a long time. "I'm staying next season for sure, it's clear," Salah said.